MALARIA - INDIA (06): MUMBAI
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Thu 5 Aug 2010
Source: The Times of India, Press Trust of India (PTI) report [edited]
<http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/Mumbai-malaria-death-toll-reaches-45/articleshow/6262679.cms>


Health officials said today [5 Aug 2010] 2 persons died of malaria
last night [in Mumbai], taking the death toll to 6 due to the disease
since August [2010]. The fresh victims of malaria include a
50-year-old man, a resident of Goregaon, and a 16-year-old boy, a
resident of Haji Ali, they said.

Altogether, over 45 deaths have been reported due to malaria since
January this year [2010], they said.

Over 200 persons suffering from malaria were admitted to the hospital
today [5 Aug 2010], they said, adding that total number of malaria
patients admitted to various city hospitals since August has reached to 988.

Even as the number of cases due to malaria keep rising per day and at
least one death is being reported due to the disease, Mumbai Mayor
Shraddha Jadhav today [5 Aug 2010] said BMC [Brihanmumbai Municipal
Corporation] has been successful in preventing malaria cases in the city.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the last report from 22 Jul 2010, ProMED-mail cited Mumbai city
officials reporting 8614 malaria cases in 14 days or more than 600
cases daily. In this comparison, 200 cases daily is a reduction.
However, the accuracy of the reporting are not known. - Mod.EP]

[Mumbai can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map
of India at <http://healthmap.org/r/00BT>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
